.TH LONGHORN 1 "2026-03-29" "longhorn 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
longhorn \- a fast launcher with aero glass aesthetics
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B longhorn
[\fB\-b\fR]
[\fB\-l\fR \fIlines\fR]
[\fB\-p\fR \fIprompt\fR]
[\fB\-fn\fR \fIfont\fR]
[\fB\-fs\fR \fIsize\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B longhorn
reads newline\-delimited items from stdin and presents a graphical menu
with a frosted glass aesthetic.
The user can type to filter items and press Enter to select one.
The selected item is printed to stdout.
.PP
If no item is selected (e.g. the user presses Escape),
.B longhorn
exits with status 1 and prints nothing.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-b
Position the menu at the bottom of the screen instead of the top.
.TP
.BI \-l " lines"
Number of vertical lines to display.
A value of 0 (the default) uses a single horizontal line.
.TP
.BI \-p " prompt"
Set the prompt string.
The default prompt is
.BR > .
.TP
.BI \-fn " font"
Path to a TrueType font file to use for rendering.
If not specified, a built\-in default is used.
.TP
.BI \-fs " size"
Font size in points.
The default is 16.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
An item was selected and printed to stdout.
.TP
.B 1
No item was selected, or an error occurred.
.SH EXAMPLES
Launch a program from a list:
.PP
.nf
echo \-e "firefox\enthunderbird\engimp" | longhorn
.fi
.PP
Use with dmenu\-compatible scripts:
.PP
.nf
dmenu_path | longhorn \-l 10 \-p "run:"
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR dmenu (1),
.BR rofi (1)
